<section id="kickstart"
         xreflabel="kickstart">
  <title>
  Kickstart
  </title>

  <section>
    <title>
    Definition
    </title>

    <para>
    Specifies the <varname>PATH</varname> to a default kickstart file for the 
    distribution. The file is included in the 
    <filename>initrd.img</filename>, and a <constant>ks=file:/</constant>
    <varname>BASENAME</varname> 
    parameter is added to the kernel boot arguments for 
    <emphasis role="strong"><xref linkend="bootiso" /></emphasis>, 
    <emphasis role="strong"><xref linkend="diskboot-image" /></emphasis> and all
    <emphasis role="strong"><xref linkend="iso" /></emphasis> 
    images.</para> 

    <para>
    The file is also included at the root of the installation tree for the 
    published distribution (e.g. 
    http://server.company.com/distributions/$ID/os/ks.cfg), where it can be
    accessed during network boot (PXE) and virtual machine installations.
    </para>

    <para>
    This module is a member of the <emphasis role="strong">installer</emphasis>
    module group.
    </para>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>
    Syntax
    </title>

    <programlisting>
[&lt;kickstart [enabled=BOOLEAN]&gt;PATH&lt;/kickstart&gt;]
    </programlisting>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>
    Attributes
    </title>

    <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>
      enabled
      </term>

      <listitem>
      <para>
      See Common Attribute <emphasis><xref linkend="enabled" /></emphasis>.
      </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>
    Examples
    </title>

    <informalexample>
    <programlisting>
&lt;kickstart&gt;ks.cfg&lt;/kickstart&gt;
    </programlisting>
    </informalexample>
  </section>

